  "prompt": "In simple words, how do the air brakes on trucks work?",
  "response": "Air brakes on trucks work by using compressed air to apply brake pressure. Here's a simple breakdown:\n\n1. A compressor pumps air into storage tanks on the truck\n\n2. When the driver presses the brake pedal, compressed air is released through a series of valves\n\n3. This air pressure pushes brake pads or shoes against the wheel drums, creating friction that slows or stops the truck\n\n4. The more the driver presses the pedal, the more air pressure is applied, creating stronger braking\n\nThe system is designed to be fail-safe - if air pressure is lost, the brakes automatically apply to stop the truck.",
